Paste-ready paragraph for the Results chapter:
-----------------------------------------------
  Genome-wide linkage disequilibrium (LD) decay was estimated from
  pairwise r^2 values computed in PLINK for all SNP pairs within
  2.5 Mb across the seven barley chromosomes in the 290 wild barley
  accessions. Mean r^2 within 1-kb distance bins was smoothed using
  a pair-count-weighted LOESS curve (span = 0.10). The smoothed
  genome-wide r^2 decayed from ~0.27 at short distances toward an
  asymptote of ~0.10 at 2.5 Mb, crossing r^2 = 0.2 at ~188 kb.
  This distance was adopted as the half-width of the +/- 188 kb
  candidate-gene search window around lead SNPs from the GWAS.

